# Day 07 - LLM Fine-Tuning with LoRA & PEFT using Hugging Face on H200

## Overview

This session introduced the concepts of Large Language Model (LLM) fine-tuning using Parameter-Efficient Fine-Tuning (PEFT) techniques and Low-Rank Adaptation (LoRA). The session also explored the Hugging Face ecosystem and GPU-accelerated model training on NVIDIA H200 GPUs.

## Topics Covered

* Introduction to Large Language Models (LLMs)
* Fine-Tuning vs Prompt Engineering
* Parameter-Efficient Fine-Tuning (PEFT)
* Low-Rank Adaptation (LoRA)
* Hugging Face Transformers Library
* Hugging Face Datasets
* GPU-Accelerated Training on H200
* Model Inference and Evaluation

## Activities Completed

* Explored the Hugging Face ecosystem for LLM development.
* Understood the working principles of LoRA and PEFT.
* Learned how to fine-tune pre-trained language models efficiently.
* Examined GPU-accelerated training workflows using NVIDIA H200 GPUs.
* Evaluated the benefits of parameter-efficient fine-tuning techniques.

## Files Included

* LLM Fine-Tuning notebooks
* LoRA implementation examples
* PEFT practical exercises
* Hugging Face demonstrations

## Key Learnings

* Understanding the architecture and capabilities of Large Language Models.
* Difference between full model fine-tuning and parameter-efficient fine-tuning.
* Working principles of LoRA for reducing computational requirements.
* Using Hugging Face libraries for loading, training, and evaluating transformer models.
* Importance of GPU acceleration for efficient LLM training and inference.

## Outcome

Successfully gained foundational knowledge of LLM fine-tuning using LoRA and PEFT techniques while exploring the Hugging Face ecosystem and GPU-accelerated AI model development on NVIDIA H200 hardware.
